<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10036</anchor> <rss>erct-002S.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-002S</addr>  <route>erct-002S.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Being <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002S.agda" type="external">erct-002S.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>The type of <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinverses</link> of a given function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10037</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <link href="erct-002Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002Q" title="Sections of sections are unique">Sections of sections</link> and <link href="erct-002R.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002R" title="Retractions of retractions are unique">retractions of retractions</link> are unique.
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10038</anchor> <rss>erct-0046.rss.xml</rss>  <addr>erct-0046</addr>  <route>erct-0046.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Coherence of different notions of equivalence</title>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10039</anchor>      <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-0046.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0046" title="Coherence of different notions of equivalence">Coherence of different notions of equivalence</link> › coherence of <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinverses</link></title> <parent>erct-0046</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10040</anchor> <rss>erct-002Q.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002Q</addr>  <route>erct-002Q.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">Sections</link> of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link> are unique</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002Q.agda" type="external">erct-002Q.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> be a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> of some <tex>r \colon  B \to  A</tex>; the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link> of <tex>f</tex> is, then, a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10041</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Using the <link href="erct-0015.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0015" title="The univalence principle for dependent functions">univalence principle for dependent function spaces</link>, we can see that the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link> of <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f \circ  -</tex> at <tex>1_{ B }</tex>, using the <link href="erct-0023.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0023" title="Path object structure on sections">univalence principle for sections</link>.</p>

 <p>To show that the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link> of <tex>f</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>, we may assume beforehand that we have such a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> of <tex>f</tex>; therefore, because we have assumed a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</link> of <tex>f</tex> already, we know that <tex>f</tex> is <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> and <link href="erct-002N.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002N" title="Biinvertible maps are contractible">therefore</link> that <tex>f</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>. By <ref addr="erct-0026" href="erct-0026.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>, it suffices to show that the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f \circ  -</tex> at <tex>1_{ B }</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>, which follows via <ref addr="erct-001K" href="erct-001K.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> and <ref addr="erct-002O" href="erct-002O.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10042</anchor> <rss>erct-002R.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002R</addr>  <route>erct-002R.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">Retractions</link> of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retractions</link> are unique</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002R.agda" type="external">erct-002R.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> be a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</link> of some <tex>s \colon  B \to  A</tex>; the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retractions</link> of <tex>f</tex> is, then, a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10043</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Analogous to the <link href="erct-002Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002Q" title="Sections of sections are unique">corresponding result for sections of sections</link>, using the fact that the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retractions</link> of <tex>f</tex> can be seen to be a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>- \circ  f</tex> at <tex>1_{ A }</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10044</anchor> <rss>erct-002S.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-002S</addr>  <route>erct-002S.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Being <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002S.agda" type="external">erct-002S.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>The type of <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinverses</link> of a given function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10045</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <link href="erct-002Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002Q" title="Sections of sections are unique">Sections of sections</link> and <link href="erct-002R.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002R" title="Retractions of retractions are unique">retractions of retractions</link> are unique.
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10046</anchor> <rss>erct-0045.rss.xml</rss>  <addr>erct-0045</addr>  <route>erct-0045.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-0046.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0046" title="Coherence of different notions of equivalence">Coherence of different notions of equivalence</link> › coherence of <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">inverses</link></title> <parent>erct-0046</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10047</anchor> <rss>erct-0041.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-0041</addr>  <route>erct-0041.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>The <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">coherent remainder</link> of a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0041.agda" type="external">erct-0041.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Given a function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> and a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> <tex>g \colon  B \to  A</tex> witnessed by <tex>\epsilon \colon  f \circ  g =  1_{ B }</tex>, we define the <em><strong>coherent remainder</strong></em> of <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( g, \epsilon \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> to be the following sum:</p><tex display="block">   \mathsf {coherentRemainder}_{ f } \mathopen {} \left ( g, \epsilon \right ) \mathclose {}  : \equiv   \mathchoice { \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \eta : g \circ  f  \sim   1_{ A } \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \eta : g \circ  f  \sim   1_{ A } \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \eta : g \circ  f  \sim   1_{ A } \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \eta : g \circ  f  \sim   1_{ A } \right ) \mathclose {} } }    \mathsf {act}_{ f } \circ   \eta   \sim   \epsilon   \circ  f </tex><p>For any <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex>, it is evident that the type of <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">inverses</link> to <tex>f</tex> is (up to reassociation) precisely the dependent sum <tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \mathsf {section} \, f \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \mathsf {section} \, f \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \mathsf {section} \, f \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \mathsf {section} \, f \right ) \mathclose {} } } \mathsf {coherentRemainder}_{ f }</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10048</anchor> <rss>erct-0042.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-0042</addr>  <route>erct-0042.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-0041.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0041" title="The coherent remainder of a section">Coherent remainder</link> as a <link href="erct-0010.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0010" title="Path object">path object</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0042.agda" type="external">erct-0042.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> be a function equipped with a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> <tex>\sigma   \equiv   \mathopen {} \left ( g \colon  B \to  A, \epsilon \colon  f \circ  g =  1_{ B } \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>. We can equip the <link href="erct-0041.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0041" title="The coherent remainder of a section">coherent remainder</link> of <tex>\sigma</tex> with the structure of a <link href="erct-0010.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0010" title="Path object">path object</link> as follows:</p><ol><li>
  We equip <tex>g \circ  f \sim   1_{ A }</tex> with the following <link href="erct-001C.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001C" title="Dependent product of path objects">dependent product</link> of <link href="erct-0013.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0013" title="The intrinsic path object">intrinsic path object</link> structures:
  <tex display="block">     \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }            \mathopen {} \left (       g \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {}  = x      \right ) \mathclose {}      ^{=}    </tex></li>
 <li>
  For each <tex>\eta \colon  g \circ  f \sim 1_{ A }</tex>, we likewise equip <tex>\mathsf {act}_{ f } \circ \eta \sim   \epsilon \circ  f</tex> with the following <link href="erct-001C.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001C" title="Dependent product of path objects">dependent product</link> of <link href="erct-0013.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0013" title="The intrinsic path object">intrinsic path object</link> structures:
  <tex display="block">     \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }            \mathopen {} \left (        \mathsf {act}_{ f } \mathopen {} \left ( \eta  x \right ) \mathclose {}  =  \epsilon \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {}       \right ) \mathclose {}      ^{=}    </tex></li>
 <li><p>We exhibit the latter as a <link href="erct-0032.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0032" title="Cartesian family of path objects">cartesian family of path objects</link> over the former with the cleaving that for <tex>\eta _0, \eta _1 \colon  g \circ  f \sim   1_{ A }</tex> and <tex>\eta _{01} \colon   \eta _0  \sim   \eta _1</tex> defines <tex>\eta _{01}^* \colon   \mathsf {act}_{ f } \circ \eta _1 \sim   \epsilon \circ  f  \to   \mathsf {act}_{ f } \circ   \eta _0 \sim \epsilon \circ  f</tex> as follows:</p>
  <tex display="block">     \begin {aligned}     &amp; \eta _{01}^* \chi  : \equiv       \lambda x \mathpunct {.}       \mathsf {act}_{ \mathsf {act}_{ f } } \mathopen {} \left ( \eta _{01}x \right ) \mathclose {} \cdot   \chi  x     \end {aligned}   </tex></li></ol><p>With this cleaving in mind, finally define <tex>\mathsf {coherentRemainder}_{ f } \sigma</tex> to be the following <link href="erct-0036.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0036" title="Contravariant sum of cartesian families of path objects">contravariant sum</link> of <link href="erct-0010.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0010" title="Path object">path objects</link>:</p><tex display="block">   \mathsf {coherentRemainder}_{ f } \sigma  : \equiv    \mathchoice { \textstyle \int _{ \mathopen {} \left (     \eta :    \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }          \mathopen {} \left ( g \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {} =x \right ) \mathclose {}     ^{=}    \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \int _{ \mathopen {} \left (     \eta :    \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }          \mathopen {} \left ( g \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {} =x \right ) \mathclose {}     ^{=}    \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \int _{ \mathopen {} \left (     \eta :    \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }          \mathopen {} \left ( g \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {} =x \right ) \mathclose {}     ^{=}    \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \int _{ \mathopen {} \left (     \eta :    \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }          \mathopen {} \left ( g \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {} =x \right ) \mathclose {}     ^{=}    \right ) \mathclose {} } }    \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }        \mathopen {} \left (      \mathsf {act}_{ f } \mathopen {} \left ( \eta  x \right ) \mathclose {}  =  \epsilon \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {}     \right ) \mathclose {}    ^{=}  </tex><p>Given elements <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( \eta _0, \chi _0 \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> and <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( \eta _1, \chi _1 \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> of <tex>\mathsf {coherentRemainder}_{ f } \sigma</tex>, the resulting type <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( \eta _0, \chi _0 \right ) \mathclose {} \cong _{ \mathsf {coherentRemainder}_{ f } \sigma } \mathopen {} \left ( \eta _1, \chi _1 \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> is definitionally equivalent to the following dependent sum:</p><tex display="block">   \mathchoice { \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \eta _{01}: \eta _0 \sim   \eta _1 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \eta _{01}: \eta _0 \sim   \eta _1 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \eta _{01}: \eta _0 \sim   \eta _1 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \eta _{01}: \eta _0 \sim   \eta _1 \right ) \mathclose {} } }    \chi _0  \sim   \lambda x \mathpunct {.}   \mathsf {act}_{ \mathsf {act}_{ f } } \mathopen {} \left ( \eta _{01}x \right ) \mathclose {} \cdot   \chi _1 x </tex></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10049</anchor> <rss>erct-0043.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-0043</addr>  <route>erct-0043.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>The <link href="erct-0041.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0041" title="The coherent remainder of a section">coherent remainder</link> of a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0043.agda" type="external">erct-0043.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>\sigma \equiv \mathopen {} \left ( g \colon  B \to  A, \epsilon \colon  f \circ  g = 1_{ B } \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> be a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> of a function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex>. Then the <link href="erct-0041.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0041" title="The coherent remainder of a section">coherent remainder</link> of <tex>\sigma</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10050</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By <ref addr="erct-0026" href="erct-0026.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>, we may argue that <tex>\mathsf {coherentRemainder}_{ f } \sigma</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>. We let <tex>P</tex> be the following type defined using <link href="erct-0010.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0010" title="Path object">path object</link> structure of <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fibers</link> given in <ref addr="erct-001R" href="erct-001R.xml" taxon="Example"/>:</p>
 <tex display="block">    \begin {aligned}    P &amp;: \equiv      \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }      \mathopen {} \left ( g \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {} , \epsilon \mathopen {} \left ( fx \right ) \mathclose {} \right ) \mathclose {}      \cong _{ \mathsf {fiber} \, f \, \mathopen {} \left ( fx \right ) \mathclose {} }     \mathopen {} \left ( x, \mathsf {refl} \right ) \mathclose {}      \\     P &amp; \equiv      \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }      \mathchoice { \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( p : g \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {}  = x \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( p : g \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {}  = x \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( p : g \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {}  = x \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( p : g \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {}  = x \right ) \mathclose {} } }      \epsilon \mathopen {} \left ( fx \right ) \mathclose {}  =  \mathsf {act}_{ f } p \cdot   \mathsf {refl}     \end {aligned}  </tex>

 <p>It is not difficult to show using <ref addr="erct-0042" href="erct-0042.xml" taxon="Definition"/> that <tex>\mathsf {coherentRemainder}_{ f } \sigma</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of <tex>P</tex>; we will not need the further fact that it is <em>equivalent</em> to <tex>P</tex>.</p>

 <p>Therefore, it remains to show that <tex>P</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>. Without loss of generality, we may assume that we have some <tex>h: P</tex>. By <ref addr="erct-001B" href="erct-001B.xml" taxon="Corollary"/>, we may fix <tex>x:A</tex> and prove that <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( g \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {} , \epsilon \mathopen {} \left ( fx \right ) \mathclose {} \right ) \mathclose {} \cong _{ \mathsf {fiber} \, f \, \mathopen {} \left ( fx \right ) \mathclose {} } \mathopen {} \left ( x, \mathsf {refl} \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>. Of course, this is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of the identification type <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( g \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {} , \epsilon \mathopen {} \left ( fx \right ) \mathclose {} \right ) \mathclose {} =_{ \mathsf {fiber} \, f \, \mathopen {} \left ( fx \right ) \mathclose {} } \mathopen {} \left ( x, \mathsf {refl} \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> and so by <ref addr="erct-0026" href="erct-0026.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> it is enough to prove that the latter is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>. In fact, we will deduce this via <ref addr="erct-002T" href="erct-002T.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> by observing that the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> at <tex>fx</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link>: using our assumption <tex>h:P</tex> and the distributivity of products over sums, we may construct a retraction of <tex>f</tex> exhibiting <tex>f</tex> as <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> and thus by <ref addr="erct-002N" href="erct-002N.xml" taxon="Corollary"/> <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10051</anchor> <rss>erct-0044.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-0044</addr>  <route>erct-0044.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Being <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">invertible</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0044.agda" type="external">erct-0044.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>For any function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex>, the type of <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">inverses</link> to <tex>f</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10052</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Without loss of generality, we may assume that <tex>f</tex> has an <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">inverse</link> <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( g, \epsilon , \eta , \chi \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>. By <ref addr="erct-0026" href="erct-0026.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>, it suffices to argue that the type of <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">inverses</link> to <tex>f</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>; the type of <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">inverses</link> to <tex>f</tex> is in fact equivalent to the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link> equipped with a <link href="erct-0041.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0041" title="The coherent remainder of a section">coherent remainder</link>:</p>
 <tex display="block">    \mathchoice { \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \sigma : \mathsf {section} \, f \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \sigma : \mathsf {section} \, f \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \sigma : \mathsf {section} \, f \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \sigma : \mathsf {section} \, f \right ) \mathclose {} } }     \mathsf {coherentRemainder}_{ f } \sigma   </tex>

 <p>By <ref addr="erct-001M" href="erct-001M.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>, it suffices to show that the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link> to <tex>f</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link> and that for every such <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link>, the <link href="erct-0041.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0041" title="The coherent remainder of a section">coherent remainder</link> thereof is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>. The latter is <ref addr="erct-0043" href="erct-0043.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>, and the former follows from <ref addr="erct-002Q" href="erct-002Q.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> by means of the <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</link> <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( g, \eta \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10053</anchor> <rss>erct-0047.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-0047</addr>  <route>erct-0047.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Being an <link href="erct-003K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003K" title="Embedding">embedding</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0047.agda" type="external">erct-0047.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>That a given function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is an <link href="erct-003K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003K" title="Embedding">embedding</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10054</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By <ref addr="erct-001B" href="erct-001B.xml" taxon="Corollary"/> and <ref addr="erct-0044" href="erct-0044.xml" taxon="Corollary"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10055</anchor> <rss>erct-003G.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-003G</addr>  <route>erct-003G.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>10</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Being <link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">bijective</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003G.agda" type="external">erct-003G.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>That a given map <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">bijective</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10056</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>10</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By <ref addr="erct-002B" href="erct-002B.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>, <ref addr="erct-0047" href="erct-0047.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> via <ref addr="erct-001M" href="erct-001M.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10057</anchor> <rss>erct-002Q.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002Q</addr>  <route>erct-002Q.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">Sections</link> of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link> are unique</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002Q.agda" type="external">erct-002Q.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> be a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> of some <tex>r \colon  B \to  A</tex>; the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link> of <tex>f</tex> is, then, a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10058</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-002Q</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Using the <link href="erct-0015.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0015" title="The univalence principle for dependent functions">univalence principle for dependent function spaces</link>, we can see that the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link> of <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f \circ  -</tex> at <tex>1_{ B }</tex>, using the <link href="erct-0023.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0023" title="Path object structure on sections">univalence principle for sections</link>.</p>

 <p>To show that the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link> of <tex>f</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>, we may assume beforehand that we have such a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> of <tex>f</tex>; therefore, because we have assumed a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</link> of <tex>f</tex> already, we know that <tex>f</tex> is <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> and <link href="erct-002N.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002N" title="Biinvertible maps are contractible">therefore</link> that <tex>f</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>. By <ref addr="erct-0026" href="erct-0026.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>, it suffices to show that the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f \circ  -</tex> at <tex>1_{ B }</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>, which follows via <ref addr="erct-001K" href="erct-001K.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> and <ref addr="erct-002O" href="erct-002O.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10059</anchor> <rss>erct-002R.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002R</addr>  <route>erct-002R.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">Retractions</link> of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retractions</link> are unique</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002R.agda" type="external">erct-002R.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> be a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</link> of some <tex>s \colon  B \to  A</tex>; the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retractions</link> of <tex>f</tex> is, then, a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10060</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-002R</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Analogous to the <link href="erct-002Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002Q" title="Sections of sections are unique">corresponding result for sections of sections</link>, using the fact that the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retractions</link> of <tex>f</tex> can be seen to be a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>- \circ  f</tex> at <tex>1_{ A }</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10061</anchor> <rss>erct-001I.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001I</addr>  <route>erct-001I.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Proposition</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001I.agda" type="external">erct-001I.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is said to be a <em><strong>proposition</strong></em> when every <tex>x:A</tex>, the type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible with centre</link> <tex>x</tex>, i.e. all elements of <tex>A</tex> are identified.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10062</anchor> <rss>erct-000U.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000U</addr>  <route>erct-000U.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Biinverse</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000U.agda" type="external">erct-000U.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em><strong>biinverse</strong></em> to a function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is defined to be a pair of a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> and a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</link> to <tex>f</tex>. We will refer to a function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> equipped with a biinverse as a <em><strong>biinvertible function</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10063</anchor> <rss>erct-003I.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-003I</addr>  <route>erct-003I.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>10</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000V.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000V" title="Equivalence of types">Equivalence</link> between <link href="erct-000V.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000V" title="Equivalence of types">equivalences</link> and <link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">bijections</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003I.agda" type="external">erct-003I.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>The correspondence between <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> and <link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">bijective</link> maps of <ref addr="erct-003H" href="erct-003H.xml" taxon="Corollary"/> and <ref addr="erct-002Z" href="erct-002Z.xml" taxon="Corollary"/> lifts to an <link href="erct-000V.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000V" title="Equivalence of types">equivalence</link> from the type of <link href="erct-000V.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000V" title="Equivalence of types">equivalences</link> to the type of <link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">bijections</link>.</p>
 
   
